attributes.title: MoMA - Design Takes on Risk
attributes.description: he best part about working on this fun project with MoMA in NYC was not the project although that was pretty epic. The best part was writing the proposal and our creative response. The brief asked us to discuss fear in our daily lives and how we might create a microsite to convey this adaptation to fear.

attributes.title: Stussy
attributes.description: The last flash project I developed. The last flash project anybody developed. Insanely well designed site with content stream made from custom tagging system we pioneered that flowed in content from over 100 stores, 3 continents and the main Stussy brand team.

attributes.title: Nike FuelBand
attributes.description: We created and managed a large content team running events and editorial content for Nilke FueBand. Over 60 events in over the summer.

attributes.title: OKML
attributes.description: OKML was a 6 week workshop helping creatives complete Arduino based installations. The workshop culminated in an art show in Dogpatch San Francisco, CA.

attributes.title: Mitch Ranger
attributes.description: Experimental photography portfolio for Mitch Ranger. Dynamically created color pallate based on the dominant color in the each photograph.

attributes.title: Falling Whistles White House Campaign
attributes.description: Created an iPad application that let users take a photo on themselves that was turned into an African style campaign poster. The photos were then faxed one by one to the Whitehouse to garner support for effort to end the war in the Congo.
